TY  - JOUR
AU  - Seidmann, Daniel J.
AU  - Winter, Eyal
T1  - A Theory of Gradual Coalition Formation
PY  - 1998
Y1  - 1998/10/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00069
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 65
IS  - 4
SP  - 793
EP  - 815
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We study noncooperative multilateral bargaining games, based on underlying TU games, in which coalitions can renegotiate their agreements. We distinguish between models in which players continue to bargain after implementing agreements (“reversible actions”) and models in which players who implement agreements must leave the game (“irreversible actions”). We show that renegotiation always results in formation of the grand coalition if actions are reversible, but that the process may otherwise end with smaller coalitions. On the other hand, we show that the grand coalition cannot form in one step if the core of the game is empty, irrespective of the reversibility of actions.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00069
ER  - 



