TY  - JOUR
AU  - Evans, Martin D. D.
T1  - Dividend Variability and Stock Market Swings
PY  - 1998
Y1  - 1998/10/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00065
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 65
IS  - 4
SP  - 711
EP  - 740
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper examines the extent to which swings in stock prices can be related to variations in the discounted value of expected future dividends when investors face uncertainty about their future behaviour. I develop an econometric model that accounts for the instability of U.S. dividend growth and discount rates during the past 120 years. Estimates of the model reveal that changing forecasts of future dividend growth account for more than 90% of the predictable variations in dividend-prices. The estimates also imply that instability in the dividend and discount rate processes contribute significantly to the predictability of long-horizon stock returns.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00065
ER  - 



